    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="699"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d699">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18106</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Funston</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of War</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1349–A. Following just received from Colonel Sibley, Marathon, Texas: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Carl Halter, superintendent and six employees International Mining
                            Company, captured by raiding Mexicans Saturday at Mexican terminal of
                            tramway at Boquillas, succeeded in escaping yesterday morning by
                            overpowering guard of three men about twenty-five miles south of border
                            arriving here this morning. At Boquillas they turned prisoners over to
                            sheriff Walters of Alpine. Deemer and a negro are the only Americans now
                            missing. Halter says Deemer riding on a wagon being taken south was
                            assured He would not be harmed. Mexicans believed to be same party that
                            looted Sierra-Mouava, Coahuilla and who captured Juan Bilboa. Officer in
                            charge of party stated you people have been looking for Villa. I will
                            show him to you in Lagina [Laguna].</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Funston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
